Introduction
This utility provides basic Archos Hardware Emulation
for more information please visit http://archopen.org

Basic Compilation Instrustions:

Summary
The steps to get emu2 compiled are

    * Summary
    * Login to the Project CVS
    * Download Emu2 source from CVS
    * Get the other required sources and tools
    * Set paths
    * Make
    * Using Emu2 



Login to the Project CVS

    * If you are running linux you will likely have a CVS client already installed...
    * if you need one, take a look at http://sourceforge.net/docs/B01/#cvs_client
    * using the cvs commandline utility in a bash shell:
          o first cd to a folder where you want the sourcecode to be downloaded to, then: 

$ cvs -d:pserver:anonymous@cvs.sourceforge.net:/cvsroot/linav login


    * just hit
      ENTER
      when prompted for a password 

Download Emu2 source from CVS

$ cvs checkout emu2


Get the other required sources and tools
You will need the following tools and source files installed

    * G++ (and dependancies)
    * make (and dependancies)
    * libx11-dev (and dependancies)
    * libreadline5-dev (and dependancies) 

Set paths
You will also need to set the paths so that the make command will know where to find the development sources:

$ PATH=$PATH:/usr/X11R6
$ PATH=$PATH:/usr/local/bin
$ export PATH


Make
cd to the folder you upacked the Emu2 source to. if you ls, you should see a file named makefile
you can now

$ make


emu2 Setup:
------------------------------------

to use emu2 you have to get it from the sourceforge cvs. Next you have to compile emu2. After you get Emu2 compiled, get the source for gdoom(it is part of the medios module on sf) and compile it. Copy 'medios.bin' to the emu2 folder. now you need to make a hard drive image for the emulator. Use dd to create a blank 50MB file called HD.bin

$ dd if=/dev/zero of=HD.bin seek=100 count=1 bs=1M


now format this file so that it has the structure of a formated hard drive.

$ /sbin/mkfs.vfat HD.bin


create a folder as a mountpoint for your HD.bin

$ sudo mkdir /mnt/archos


USAGE EXAMPLE:
--------------------------
now mount the HD.bin and copy over the .wads for doom.

$ sudo mount -o loop HD.bin /mnt/archos


to run emu2 type the following.

$ ./emu -f medios.bin

GETTING HELP:
-----------------
type help to see command list
type exit to exit emulator


